"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-when-will-gerda-steyn-run-the-paris-olympics-2024-marathon-question-exclusive-date-result\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbWhen will Gerda Steyn run the Paris Olympics 2024 marathon?  Fresh off her record Comrades Marathon run, SA's ultra-marathon queen Gerda Steyn will turn her attention to the Paris Olympics marathon.  South Africa's ultra-marathon queenGerda Steynsmashed her ownComrades Marathon'up' record inemphatic fashionon Sunday.  Steyn, 34, will now turn her attention to themarathonat the2024 Paris Olympics.  The women's marathon is set forSunday, 11 August- in exactly61days' time.  Mark that date in your diaryNOW!  As reported byThe South African website, Team SA will havethreerepresentatives in the women's marathon in Paris.  Steyn, who finished15thin the most recent Olympics held in Tokyo, holds the South African marathon record of2:24:03.  She will be joined on the start line byCian OldknowandIrvette van Zyl, who will be attending her third Olympics.  Meanwhile, SteynwonherthirdComrades Marathon title - and second 'up' run - in a new record time of 5:49:46 on Sunday.  She picked upR2 075 000for her win, courtesy ofR825 000for winning,R500 000for the new record,R500 000for a fastest ever average pace,R200 000for being a South African winner andR50 000for the Cell C Hot Spot incentive.  The race started at05:30at the Durban City Hall and the final cut-off gun sounded 12 hours later at17:30at the Hollywoodbets Scottsville Racecourse.  The official route distance was85.91km, making this year's race theshortestever Comrades Marathon.  Earlier, as reported byThe South African website, the Netherlands'Piet Wiersmawonthe men's title.  Wiersma, 26, crossed the finish line in an unofficial time of 5:25:01.  South Africa'sDan Moselakwefinished second in 5:25:45, with Ethiopia'sDegefa Lafeborounding out the podium in 5:27:49.  Wiersma finished second in last year's 'down' run by just three seconds.  His 2023 time was the fastest ever by a Comrades Marathondebutant.  He wonR825 000for his efforts and was the first non-South African winner of the race since Zimbabwe'sStephen Muzhingitriumphed in 2011.  Win - R825 000  Record - R500 000  Best average pace - R500 000  SA athlete - R200 000  KwaZulu-Natal athlete - R60 000  Cell C Hot Spot - R50 000  TOTAL: R2 135 000  Men  Leonid Shvetsov(Russia) - 5.24.39 (set in 2008)  Women  Gerda Steyn (South Africa) - 5.49:46 (set in 2024)  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky 